1 SECTION 2. IC 7.1-3-4-6, AS AMENDED BY P.L.167-2024,
2 SECTION 5, IS AMENDED TO READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE
3 JULY 1, 2026]: Sec. 6. (a) The holder of a beer retailer's permit shall
4 be entitled to purchase beer for sale under the permit only from a
5 permittee entitled to sell to the beer retailer under this title. A beer
6 retailer shall be entitled to possess beer and sell beer at retail to a
7 customer for consumption on the licensed premises. A beer retailer also
8 shall be entitled to sell beer to a customer and deliver beer in
9 permissible containers to the customer on the licensed premises, or to
10 the customer's house. This delivery may only be performed by the
11 permit holder or an employee who holds an employee permit. The
12 permit holder shall maintain a written record of each delivery for at
13 least one (1) year that shows the customer's name, location of delivery,
14 and quantity sold. Subject to subsection (g), a beer retailer also may
15 prepare and package beer in qualified containers for sale and delivery
16 to a customer on the licensed premises for consumption off the licensed
17 premises.
18 (b) A beer retailer shall not be entitled to sell beer at wholesale. A
19 beer retailer shall not be entitled to sell and deliver beer on the street
20 or at the curb outside the licensed premises, nor shall a beer retailer be
21 entitled to sell beer at a place other than the licensed premises.
22 However, a beer retailer may offer food service (excluding alcoholic
23 beverages) to a patron who is outside the licensed premises by
24 transacting business through a window in the licensed premises.
25 (c) A beer retailer shall be entitled to sell and deliver warm or cold
26 beer for carry out, or for at-home delivery, in barrels or other
27 commercial containers in a quantity that does not exceed fifteen and
28 one-half (15 1/2) gallons at any one (1) time. A beer retailer that
29 delivers beer to a customer's residence must require the customer to
30 provide proof of age in accordance with IC 7.1-5-10-23.
31 (d) Notwithstanding IC 7.1-1-3-20, the licensed premises of the beer
32 retailer may include the beer retailer parking lot or an area adjacent to
33 the beer retailer that may only be used for the purpose of conveying
34 alcoholic beverages and other nonalcoholic items to a customer, and
35 may not be used for point of sale purposes or any other purpose. Any
36 alcoholic beverages conveyed to the customer must satisfy the
37 following:
38 (1) Alcoholic beverages that are in the sealed original containers
39 must be placed in a bag that is stamped, printed, or labeled on the
40 outside: "CONTAINS ALCOHOLIC BEVERAGES".
41 (2) Alcoholic beverages that are prepared by the beer retailer
42 must be packaged by the beer retailer in qualified containers that
